Quoting Dhandeep, our super-cool lab-admin:
now , all 70 systems in the lab can be switched on and switched off by single commands from the hostel&hellip;
Yes, that and a lot more is possible in our Software Systems Lab now. How? Read on&hellip;
The Setup We have over 70 systems with Ubuntu 10.04 LTS installed on them. There is an administrative account (let&rsquo;s call it admin for this post) and a guest (limited privilege) account on each.

Some months back in November, I had used many variants of the following script to automate the download of MIT OCW videos:
#!/bin/bash baseurl=&#34;http://www.archive.org/download/MIT_Structure_of_Computer_Programs_1986/lec&#34; urlend=&#34;b_512kb.mp4&#34; log=&#34;log_b&#34; for i in {1..7} do nohup wget -c &#34;${baseurl}$i${urlend}&#34; &gt; &#34;${log}$i&#34; &amp; done It doesn&rsquo;t really do much, just put the baseurl and urlend properly which should be common for similar links and run a for loop.
Sharing so that it may come handy to some others in similar needs.
